    "body":  "We are replacing the simple colored dots with distinct SVGs/Icons.\n\n**Objective**: \nCurrently, the agents on the main Google Map in `MapUI.tsx` are just glowing CSS dots. The `@vis.gl/react-google-maps` library supports the `AdvancedMarker` API.\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create a helper function that returns a specific Google Material Icon or SVG based on the agent\u0027s `role` (e.g. \u0027Rogue AI Terminal\u0027 -\u003e Robot Icon, \u0027Times Square Street Performer\u0027 -\u003e Star Icon).\n2. Render these inside the `\u003cAdvancedMarker\u003e` component so the map feels populated with distinct characters instead of identical dots.",
